article.description: Marlain Veal had 24 points and six assists, and Southeastern Louisiana won its 14th straight home game in a 74-63 victory over Incarnate Word on Monday.
article.headline: Southeastern Louisiana extends home winning streak to 14
article.linkText: Southeastern Louisiana extends home winning streak to 14
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Marlain Veal had 24 points and six assists, and Southeastern Louisiana won its 14th straight home game in a 74-63 victory over Incarnate Word on Monday. The Lions avenged their last loss at home against UIW on Jan. 16, 2016. Incarnate Word used a 13-1 run to get within 44-42. Veal ended SE Louisiana's drought of 4:22 for a four-point lead with 11:10 left and his basket at 2:31 gave the Lions a 65-55 lead. James Currington had 13 points and nine rebounds for Southeastern Louisiana (9-6, 2-0 Southland). Moses Greenwood added 10 points and eight boards. The Lions had a 14-point lead at intermission. Jalin Hart scored 14 points on 6-of-14 shooting for Incarnate Word (5-8, 0-2). Shawn Johnson added 13 points with seven rebounds. The Cardinals were just 3 of 14 from 3-point range and 10 of 20 at the free-throw line.
